A sharp documentary-style laboratory photograph capturing a fully assembled carbon-fiber flight armor suit undergoing a final system-wide grounding validation loop inside a cleanroom workshop. The suit is mounted vertically on an adjustable testing dummy jig. A technician sets a digital multimeter to measure resistance, placing one test probe against the helmet crown and running the secondary probe across the extreme vertices of the trailing wingtip wicks, displaying a crisp '9.2 Ohms' continuity reading on its digital window screen. Digital calipers, nitrogen flush lines, and technical tools rest neatly on a light blue ESD matting bench under cool laboratory fluorescent lighting, crisp industrial focus --ar 16:9
